@NODE "ABOUT" "What is Node-Message v1.0 ?"
                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}

I've long been thinking about setting up my board with a FIDO mailreader and/or
together with other file/message-sharing systems, but how can this be achieved?

Well, AmiExpress have some communications port ready for this purpose, but I
thought it would be easier to make a program that you could just give some
parameters once for all, instead of making stupid Arexx-scripts.

I hope some can find this little CLI/DOS util useful, to suspend/resume and
even shutdown nodes on your board.


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This program should be 100% systemfriendly coded. If any error should
occure, then the program should managed to shutdown without causing any
damage to the system.

This utility is coded in Amiga-E with inline-ASM for maximal speed-performance!

@ENDNODE



;-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



@NODE "REQUIRE" "Requirements to run this door."
                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}


I think that this program should run on any version of WB and Amiga-Dos.

If you should miss any library, then the door would give a error-message and
terminate the run automaticly without harming the system.

The door should be able to run with the ordinary libraries supported with the
original Workbench-package from Commodore. (Any revision)

Also... Arexx-libraries... :)

@ENDNODE



;-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



@NODE "INSTALL" "How to do the installation..."
                                                               @{" Go back.. " Link MAIN}

All you have to do is to copy the main executable file in this archive to
whatever directory you wish. I would advice SYS:C/.


Also, if you wish to use it together with AmiExpress v3.x+, then you should
write a command-line into your logoff-script for each node.


That's all... (Simple isn't it? :)




Functionality :


  Nodemsg <Node> <Message>

  <Node> is which node the message should be redirected to.
  <Message> is a string, like : Shutdown, Resume or Suspend.



Keep in mind :

If no argument is supported, a usage-help will appear. And if only the node-nr.
is being used as argument, then the node-nr. will also be the message to send!


@ENDNODE



